ARIX-Algo Installation
======================

Prerequisites
  - C compiler: GCC 12+, Clang 15+, or MSVC 2022
  - CMake 3.20 or higher
  - Python 3.11 or higher (optional, for Python bindings)
  - 4 GB RAM minimum
  - 2 GB free disk space
  - Linux, macOS, or Windows (via WSL recommended on Windows)

Quick Install
  1. Clone the repository:
       git clone https://github.com/ammar49-cyber/sneppx-alg.git
       cd sneppx-alg

  2. Create build directory and configure:
       mkdir build && cd build
       cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

  3. Build:
       cmake --build . -j$(nproc)

  4. Run tests:
       ctest --output-on-failure

  5. (Optional) Enable tests and benchmarks:
       cmake .. -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DARIX_BUILD_TESTS=ON -DARIX_BUILD_BENCHMARKS=ON
       cmake --build . -j$(nproc)
       ctest --output-on-failure

Platform Notes
  Linux
    Install build-essential and cmake via your package manager.
    Example (Ubuntu/Debian):
      sudo apt-get install build-essential cmake

  macOS
    Install Xcode Command Line Tools and CMake:
      xcode-select --install
      brew install cmake

  Windows
    WSL (recommended):
      Install WSL2 with Ubuntu, then follow Linux instructions.
    Native (MSVC):
      Install Visual Studio 2022 with "Desktop development with C++" workload.
      Use CMakePresets.json presets (default, release).

  Python Bindings (optional)
    Requires pybind11. Install:
      pip install pybind11
    Then configure with:
      cmake .. -DARIX_BUILD_PYTHON=ON

See docs/installation.md for detailed instructions.
